system76-driver (14.10.8~alpha) utopic; urgency=low

  * Daily WIP for 14.10.8
  * system76driver.read_dmi_id() is now failsafe when "sys_vendor" or
    "product_version" contain invalid UTF-8 data; this would never be the case
    on an actual System76 product, but the driver should politely do nothing
    when installed on non-System76 hardware
  * Add "meer1" (Meerkat) to PRODUCTS
  * Add "lemu5" (Lemur) to PRODUCTS, NEEDS_BRIGHTNESS

 -- Jason Gerard DeRose <jason@system76.com>  Mon, 26 Jan 2015 11:05:15 -0700

